@page
@model ErrorModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Error";
    Layout = "_Layout"; // Optionally, specify a shared layout page.
}

<h1 class="text-danger">Error</h1>
<h2 class="text-danger">An error occurred while processing your request.</h2>

@if (Model.ShowRequestId)
{
    <p>
        <strong>Request ID:</strong> <code>@Model.RequestId</code>
    </p>
}

<h3>Error Details</h3>
<p>We apologize for the inconvenience, but an unexpected error has occurred. Below are some details about the error:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Error Code:</strong> <!-- Display error code if available --></li>
    <li><strong>Error Message:</strong> <!-- Display error message if available --></li>
    <li><strong>Timestamp:</strong> @DateTime.Now.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss")</li>
</ul>

<h3>What You Can Do</h3>
<p>If you believe this error is due to a problem with our website or services, please contact us immediately so that we can investigate and resolve the issue.</p>
<p>If you are a developer or administrator and need to debug this issue, here are some steps you can take:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Check the error code and message for clues on what went wrong.</li>
    <li>Review the logs and stack trace if available for more information.</li>
    <li>Ensure that all necessary dependencies and configurations are set up correctly.</li>
    <li>If the error persists, consider rolling back recent changes or updates.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Development Mode</h3>
<p>
    If you are seeing this error in a development environment, it means that detailed information about the error is available for debugging purposes. However, please be cautious and do not enable the development environment for deployed applications as it can expose sensitive information to end users.
</p>
<p>
    To enable the <strong>Development</strong> environment for local debugging, set the <strong>ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT</strong> environment variable to <strong>Development</strong> and restart the application.
</p>

<h3>Contact Information</h3>
<p>If you need further assistance or have any questions, please don't hesitate to <a asp-page="/Contact">contact us</a>. We're here to help you resolve any issues.</p>